I have had a few Apple products over the years.
Phones, iPods, and a MacBook.
The last iPhone I had was a 3GS. It worked, but it didn't seem as functional as an Android. Features were weak and the performance I experienced prior to the next generation release lended credibility that updates were introduced to nerf the current model.
iPods were okay, but when my entire (PC) music library was converted to iTunes, I can honestly say that I was a little bit vexxed. I spent quite a lot of time getting my music collection into my PC, so my Walkman MP3 player and other players could have a safe and convenient place to adjust my favorite tunes.
My last unfavorite piece of Apple tech was a 17 inch MacBook Pro. I got it to replace a gaming desktop.
It failed as a game rig and further scrambled my already affected media files.
All in all, the company has apparently abandoned the ideology of "simple, powerful and affordable".
Windows based machines are a lot easier to work with and upgrade and don't require a new set of cordage every few years or stupid adapters to be functional.
